obj_significance: This recording of "Jazz Horizons" features the Susie Ibarra Quartet. Susie Ibarra is a world renowned percussionist, born in California to immigrants from the Phillipines and has worked and recorded with jazz, world, classical, and indigenous musicians. This concert was curated by the Resident Artistic Director at the time, Joshua Redman, who is a Bay Area native. This recording is found nowhere else and has never been available to the public.

label: Campbell Brothers featuring Calvin Cooke & Aubrey Ghent (Family Matinee Show, 2003)
obj_significance: This concert took place as part of the 2003 San Francisco Jazz Festival's Spring Concert series. It features the Campbell Brothers featuring Calvin Cooke & Aubrey Ghent, performing at the Family Matinee series at Herbst Theatre in San Francisco, CA.  "Sacred steel" developed in Black churches in the Southeastern United States and has since become a worldwide sensation due to players like Robert Randolph and the Campbell Brothers. Sacred steel players have a unique ability to make their instruments “sing,” and their entire performance is geared towards raising a spirit of joy and community in the audience. Calvin Cooke is an elder statesman of the instrument, having performed for years on nationally-known touring stages with the Slide Brothers and Darick Campbell, as well as performances at conventions, churches, and Folk Alliance. This recording of Campbell Brothers and Calvin Cooke is found nowhere else and has never been available to the public.

label: SFJAZZ Beacon Award Concert: A Salute to Phil Elwood (2003)
obj_significance: This event took place as part of the 21st Annual San Francisco Jazz Festival. The SFJAZZ Beacon Award honors a member of the Bay Area jazz community for his or her contributions to “preserving the traditions and encouraging the growth of jazz in the Bay Area.” In 2003, Philip Elwood, the respected jazz columnist and disc jockey highly regarded for the taste and intelligence he brings to Bay Area audiences, was presented with the Beacon Award. This event took place at the Palace of Fine Arts Theatre in San Francisco, CA. This recording is found nowhere else and has never been available to the public.

label: Celebrating the Music of Rahsaan Roland Kirk w/ Steve Turre & Talk by John Schott (2005)
obj_significance: This talk and concert took place as part of the 2005 San Francisco Jazz Festival's Spring Season concert series. This recording features a pre-concert talk with Bay Area-based John Schott on the music of Rahsaan Roland Kirk. Parts 2 and 3 feature the evening concert dedicated to the works of Rahsaan Roland Kirk, with Bay-Area-based trombonist Steve Turre and others at Herbst Theatre in San Francisco, CA.  This recording is found nowhere else and has never been available to the public.

label: Listening Party with Sam Stephenson, Green Room
obj_significance: This event took place as part of the 2010 SF Jazz Festival (Spring Season). The recording features a "Listening Party" event with Sam Stephenson, writer and one of the co-producers of the documentary "The Jazz Loft According to W. Eugene Smith".  He discusses his new book "The Jazz Loft Project", documenting the recordings and photography captured by W. Eugene Smith.  The event took place at the Green Room in the War Memorial Building in San Francisco, CA. This recording is found nowhere else and has never been available to the public.
